Package com.example.bot.spring

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EventHandler
    the interface diverse event handlers will use
    LanguageProcessor
    interface for language processing
    StorageEngine
    This interface sets the methods our classes that communicate with Databases will implement
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BookingHandler
    The class representing the event handler that is in charge of handling bookings
    ChatBotApplication
    this class serves as the main class which runs the chatbot
    Controller
    Class to represent the main controller for the bot application basically the main methods to handle the text events in the line application and reply to the user
    Customer
    Class to represent a customer of the travel agency
    CustomerTest
    The Test Case for the Customer class
    EnquiryHandler
    Class to represent the event handler in charge of enquiries.
    GeneralTour
    This class is used to represent a Tour, specificaly basic information about it.
    GeneralTourTest  
    HandlerFactory
    This Class serves as a factory for different handler Classes we use a hash map for booking in order to give each booking/query a different handler
    KitchenSinkTester  
    LoggerHandler
    Class that represents the handler that takes care of questions that aren't recognized as a booking or an enquiry about a tour.
    LuisNLP
    This class use is to process the natural language given by the user on the LINE chat app.
    MessageHandler
    Class to represent the message handler
    PSQLDatabaseEngine
    This class is used to communicate with the PSQLDatabase of the chatbot
    QuestionHandler  
    Tour
    Class to represent a specific tour (has a reference to the tour id but describes a particular instance of a tour)
    TourBooking
    Class to represent a tour booking, used whenever a customer books a tour on the line application
    TourBookingTest
    Test Cases for the TourBooking class
    TourTest
    Test case for the Tour class
